  "prompt": "What are the types of induction motors?",
  "response": "There are several types of induction motors:\n\n1. Based on Rotor Construction:\n- Squirrel Cage Induction Motor\n- Wound Rotor (Slip Ring) Induction Motor\n\n2. Based on Stator Design:\n- Single-phase Induction Motor\n- Three-phase Induction Motor\n\n3. Based on Enclosure:\n- Open Drip-Proof (ODP) Motor\n- Totally Enclosed Fan Cooled (TEFC) Motor\n- Explosion Proof Motor\n\n4. Based on Speed:\n- Low-Speed Induction Motor\n- Medium-Speed Induction Motor\n- High-Speed Induction Motor\n\n5. Special Types:\n- Brake Motor\n- Submersible Motor\n- Vertical Induction Motor\n- Crane Duty Motor\n\n6. Based on Power Supply:\n- AC Induction Motor\n- Universal Motor\n\n7. Based on Application:\n- Domestic Application Motor\n- Industrial Application Motor\n- Automotive Motor\n\nEach type has specific characteristics and is designed for different operational requirements and environments.",
